One of my favorite countries, visited twice, plan on going again whenever I get the chance. Perfect opportuntiy to test out new found spatial analysis skills in R on one of my favorite destinations. Understanding greece using technologies in R. Who said you need GIS?

library('tidyverse')    
library('ggmap')
library('sp')
library('tmap')
library('raster')
library('rgdal')
library('tigris')
library('RColorBrewer')
library('viridisLite')


If you forgot where Greece is

greece <- c(lon = 21.8243, lat = 39.0742)

greece_far <- get_map(greece, zoom = 5, scale = 1, maptype="terrain")

ggmap(greece_far)

crete <- c(lon = 24.8093, lat = 35.2401)

crete_far <- get_map(crete, zoom = 5, scale = 1, maptype="terrain")
## Map from URL : http://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?center=35.2401,24.8093&zoom=5&size=640x640&scale=1&maptype=terrain&language=en-EN&sensor=false
ggmap(crete_far)

# Get map at zoom level 13: corvallis_map
crete_map <- get_map(crete, zoom = 8, scale = 1)
## Map from URL : http://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?center=35.2401,24.8093&zoom=8&size=640x640&scale=1&maptype=terrain&language=en-EN&sensor=false
# Plot map at zoom level 13
ggmap(crete_map)
